rstood about journalistic standards=E2=80=94and implying that Young will as=
k the jury for more than $787 million in damages. He writes: =E2=80=9CIf CN=
N recognized the significance of the Dominion settlement as a cautionary ta=
le yet still chose to defame Young, that fact demonstrates the insufficienc=
y of prior monetary amounts in deterring CNN=E2=80=99s misconduct.=E2=80=9D

Meanwhile, CNN=E2=80=99s trial strategy is coming into focus. The network p=
lans to call witnesses like Ralf Otto, who works with Civil Fleet, a German=
 N.G.O. that paid Young to evacuate six Afghans. Otto will testify that You=
ng collected money in advance, yet only managed to evacuate three of the si=
x, prompting Civil Fleet to hire a different
contractor for a fraction of Young=E2=80=99s price. CNN will also present t=
estimony from George McMillan, a geopolitical analyst who met Young and cam=
e away feeling =E2=80=9Che could be a fraud.=E2=80=9D The goal is clear: to=
 convince the jury that CNN=E2=80=99s description of Young as exploitative =
wasn=E2=80=99t defamatory, but rather an accurate reflection of his reputat=
ion.

These witnesses, set to fly in from abroad, caught Young=E2=80=99s lawyers =
off guard. In response, they asked Judge Henry to reopen discovery, but he =
refused. CNN, for its part, accused Young=E2=80=99s team of intimidating th=
e witnesses by raising the specter of liability for false statements and wa=
rning of potential bad press from other outlets. As CNN attorney Tobin put =
it, =E2=80=9CThere=E2=80=99s irony in how they are offensively trying to us=
e the media.=E2=80=9D

For some reason, this trial continues to fly under the radar, apart from ri=
ght-wing outlets that are reveling in the possibility of CNN=E2=80=99s emba=
rrassment. CNN, no doubt,
hopes for a low-profile trial with an outcome as muted as Netflix=E2=80=99s=
 victory in the Our Father privacy case. But with punitive damages on the t=
able, Ron DeSantis appointees reshaping Florida=E2=80=99s appellate courts,=
 Trump allies positioned at the federal level, and a legal climate growing =
less hospitable to speech deemed harmful to the national interest, this cas=
e may go places. Also, thanks to Florida=E2=80=99s tolerance of cameras in =
the courtrooms, there=E2=80=99s a good chance it=E2=80=99ll be livestreamed=
=2E

Thanks, Eriq. I=E2=80=99ll be back on Thursday.

Matt

