          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">The next big trial =
in media and entertainment=E2=80=94assuming no surprises=E2=80=94will be <b=
>Zachary Young</b>=E2=80=99s libel case against CNN. I <u><a href=3D"https:=
//email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUc3pyODdnU=
lNVS21QQzUzbm1Nbz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3Mvc3VpbmctdGhlLW1lZGlh=
LWZvci1kZWZhbWF0aW9uLWZpbmQtYS1yZXB1YmxpY2FuLWp1ZGdlLz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249V2h=
hdCtJJTI3bStIZWFyaW5nJTJCKy0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MTIlMkYxMCUyRjI0JTI5XHUwMD=
I2dXRtX2NvbnRlbnQ9V2hhdCtJJTI3bStIZWFyaW5nJTJCKy0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MTIlM=
kYxMCUyRjI0JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbF9hY3Rpb25cdTAwMjZ1dG1fc291cmNl=
PWN1c3RvbWVyLmlvXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Rlcm09ZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwiaW50ZXJuYWw=
iOiJmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJsaW5rX2lkIjoxMDI5MzkyfQ/c87b50b10f5dc3d66e6=
5800bbfc4bafa574e7cc1983a09ff27e74d0511730414" style=3D"color:#d40000;text-=
decoration:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">covered</a></u> this disput=
e a few months ago: Young, a military vet, helped evacuate Afghans fleeing =
the Taliban, only to find himself featured in a CNN segment about =E2=80=9C=
black markets=E2=80=9D in Afghanistan that were allegedly exploiting locals=
 after Biden=E2=80=99s troop withdrawal. In Florida, Circuit Judge <b>Willi=
am Henry</b> has ruled that CNN lacked evidence that Young did anything ill=
egal, greenlighting a trial to begin on January 6 and allowing
Young to pursue punitive damages.<br/><br/>As trial day approaches, tension=
s have escalated. Young=E2=80=99s legal team, led by <b>Velvel Freedman</b>=
, deposed CNN anchor <b>Jake Tapper</b> on his salary and his views of Trum=
p. Freedman also raised the $787 million penalty Fox News paid Dominion to =
settle the voting machine vendor=E2=80=99s defamation case. Seemingly inten=
t on drawing parallels between the Dominion case and Young=E2=80=99s, Freed=
man asked Tapper whether such a punishment would be enough to deter CNN fro=
m further defamatory conduct. <br/><br/>At a court hearing I observed last =
week, CNN=E2=80=99s attorney <b>Charles Tobin</b> blasted the deposition as=
 a =E2=80=9Ctotal freak show,=E2=80=9D adding, =E2=80=9CThis was very clear=
ly an ambush deposition =E2=80=A6 designed to get Mr. Tapper to say somethi=
ng in a nice tight colloquy that they could play to a jury.=E2=80=9D <br/><=
br/>CNN has now moved to exclude mentions of Trump, Fox News, or the Domini=
on settlement at trial, arguing these subjects could inflame
sensitivities among jurors in Florida=E2=80=99s deep-red Bay County. On Mon=
day, Freedman filed an opposition brief, contending there=E2=80=99s no excl=
usion for political topics, arguing that Tapper=E2=80=99s discussion of the=
 Dominion settlement goes to what the network=E2=80=99s marquee anchor unde=
rstood about journalistic standards=E2=80=94and implying that Young will as=
k the jury for <i>more</i> than $787 million in damages. He writes: =E2=80=
=9CIf CNN recognized the significance of the Dominion settlement as a cauti=
onary tale yet still chose to defame Young, that fact demonstrates the insu=
fficiency of prior monetary amounts in deterring CNN=E2=80=99s misconduct.=
=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>Meanwhile, CNN=E2=80=99s trial strategy is coming into f=
ocus. The network plans to call witnesses like <b>Ralf Otto</b>, who works =
with Civil Fleet, a German N.G.O. that paid Young to evacuate six Afghans. =
Otto will testify that Young collected money in advance, yet only managed t=
o evacuate three of the six, prompting Civil Fleet to hire a different
contractor for a fraction of Young=E2=80=99s price. CNN will also present t=
estimony from <b>George McMillan</b>, a geopolitical analyst who met Young =
and came away feeling =E2=80=9Che could be a fraud.=E2=80=9D The goal is cl=
ear: to convince the jury that CNN=E2=80=99s description of Young as exploi=
tative wasn=E2=80=99t defamatory, but rather an accurate reflection of his =
reputation.<br/><br/>These witnesses, set to fly in from abroad, caught You=
ng=E2=80=99s lawyers off guard. In response, they asked Judge Henry to reop=
en discovery, but he refused. CNN, for its part, accused Young=E2=80=99s te=
am of intimidating the witnesses by raising the specter of liability for fa=
lse statements and warning of potential bad press from other outlets. As CN=
N attorney Tobin put it, =E2=80=9CThere=E2=80=99s irony in how they are off=
ensively trying to use the media.=E2=80=9D<br/><br/>For some reason, this t=
rial continues to fly under the radar, apart from  right-wing outlets that =
are reveling in the possibility of CNN=E2=80=99s embarrassment. CNN, no dou=
bt,
hopes for a low-profile trial with an outcome as muted as Netflix=E2=80=99s=
 victory in the <i>Our Father</i> privacy case. But with punitive damages o=
n the table, <b>Ron DeSantis</b> appointees reshaping Florida=E2=80=99s app=
ellate courts, Trump allies positioned at the federal level, and a legal cl=
imate growing less hospitable to speech deemed harmful to the national inte=
rest, this case may go places. Also, thanks to Florida=E2=80=99s tolerance =
of cameras in the courtrooms, there=E2=80=99s a good chance it=E2=80=99ll b=
e livestreamed.<br/></td>
